Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_verify_drc_mode(25.10)                          get_verify_drc_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_verify_drc_mode  -  Displays  the  following  information  about  a
       set_verify_drc_mode parameter in the Innovus console

Syntax
       get_verify_drc_mode

        [-help]

        [-area]

       [-check_illegal_trim_shapes]

       [-check_ndr_spacing]

       [-check_only]

       [-check_reverse]

       [-check_routing_halo]

       [-check_routing_halo_corner]

       [-check_same_via_cell]

       [-check_short_only]

       [-check_trim_length]

       [-check_uncolored]

       [-disable_rules]

       [-enable_post_passive_fill_check]

       [-exclude_pg_net]

       [-ignore_cell_blockage]

       [-ignore_fill_wire]

       [-ignore_non_rectangle_shapes]

       [-ignore_trial_route]

       [-layer_range]

       [-limit]

       [-max_wrong_way_halo]

       [-nonDefault]

       [-report]

       [-use_min_spacing_on_block_obs]

       [-quiet]

       Displays the following information about a set_verify_drc_mode  parame-
       ter in the Innovus console.

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Default value

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       Use  this  command  when  you want to retrieve current values of all or
       specified set_verify_drc_mode settings. If you do not specify any para-
       meter, get_verify_drc_mode returns  information  on  all  the  set_ver-
       ify_drc_mode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each get_verify_drc_mode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_verify_drc_mode

       <parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See  set_verify_drc_mode  for descriptions of the parameters you
              can specify.

       -quiet Displays the current settings for the  specified  parameters  in
              Tcl list format only.

              If  you specify -quiet without any parameters, the software dis-
              plays the current settings of all set_verify_drc_mode parameters
              in Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The following command displays  the  current  setting  of  the
                -limit parameter:

                get_verify_drc_mode -limit

                The software displays the following information:

                -limit 1000 # int, default=1000

                1000

              * The  following  command  displays the current settings for all
                set_verify_drc_mode parameters:

                get_verify_drc_mode

Related Information
              * The Identifying and Viewing Violations chapter of User Guide.

              * verify_drc

              * set_verify_drc_mode

